---
description: Flat UI surfaces — borders and focus rings, not drop shadows (performance & consistency)
globs: "**/*.tsx,**/globals.css,**/primitives/**/*.tsx"
---

# UI surfaces (speed-first)

- **Avoid decorative `shadow-*` on buttons, inputs, cards, popovers, dialogs, and menus.** Shadows increase paint/compositing work and CSS payload; prefer `border border-border`, `bg-card` / `bg-muted`, and `focus-visible:ring-*` for hierarchy.
- **Do not add** `hover:shadow-md`, `shadow-sm`, `shadow-xs`, or `shadow-lg` to new components unless there is a strong accessibility reason (e.g. a single focus affordance already covered by rings).
- **Forms:** inputs use border + ring on focus only; no box shadow for elevation.
- **Consistency:** shared primitives live in `src/ui/primitives/`; update those instead of one-off shadows in feature code.
- **Exceptions:** rare marketing hero sections may use minimal shadow only if explicitly designed; default store UI stays flat.

When touching legacy files, remove redundant shadows in the same PR if the edit is already scoped to that area.

## Migration

- Primitives under `src/ui/primitives/` are the source of truth (flat surfaces).
- A repo-wide pass removed decorative `shadow-sm` / `shadow-md` / `hover:shadow-*` / `shadow-xs` from feature `*.tsx` where safe; **`shadow-none`** is kept where explicit.
- Remaining colored or arbitrary shadows (e.g. `shadow-primary/5`) should be removed when editing those files unless design explicitly requires a glow.

